If the major failure point of any individual firing system is the heat accumulated in the barrel, why don't we use separate systems? One that feeds the projectile, and one that feeds the propellant. By using separate reloadable ammunition systems, we can at least increase the volume of fire down the barrel...no, gains would be negligible: powder still explosively expands in the rounds wake, regardless or it's origin, and the barrel would heat. The real problem isn't with volume of fire anyway, it's with accuracy and understanding our need to kill it.

